Responsabilidades do cargo:
Must be able to help with preparation and cleanup of job sites; lift and carry up to 100lbs repeatedly during the
workday; use picks and shovels to hand dig and backfill excavations; follow directions and assist foreman; 
clean up and put away tools, as well as assist with building and positioning forms for pouring concrete and dismantle forms after use; also help with cutting, grinding and demolition of concrete.

Performs grounds maintenance functions (e.g., pulling weeds, raking leaves, sweeping sidewalks, and cleaning debris); 
Clears ditches, digs holes, and performs handwork as necessary using a pick, shovel, or other hand tools; 
Waters vegetation using a hose; 
Cleans canals, drains, and tree wells; 
Operates light landscape equipment (e.g., 21” mower, leaf blower, weed eater, stick edger, and hedge trimmer); 
Operates demanding landscape equipment (e.g., 36”, 48”, self-propelled, and riding lawn mowers); 
Maintains tools and equipment to ensure safety; 
Attends safety meetings; 
Role models PPE usage; and 
Plants vegetation as instructed.  
May drive company vehicles if in possession of a non-commercial driver's license that is valid in the USA, and in good standing with the issuing authority.

greet guests immediately in a Forbes 5-star manner with a friendly and sincere welcome;
providing front desk services including completing the registration process by inputting and retrieving information from a computer system, confirming pertinent information; providing bell hop services welcoming guests and assisting with luggage to/from hotel rooms; 
assist with recreation activities at the pool area including providing guest towels, beach chairs, umbrellas, maintaining a clean area and taking pool towels to and from the laundry department; 
assist guest with recommendations for both on-property and off-property activities;
obtain in-depth knowledge of the hotel and town that the property is located to answer questions that guest may have to enhance their experience on Martha’s Vineyard.  
Driving company owned golf/utility vehicle and vehicles using valet parking service.  
Use of company owned golf/utility vehicle to shuttle guests to the downtown area which is located  within one mile of the hotel.  
Valet parking would be applicable in this task which requires driving of guest vehicles within the hotel property to and from the designated valet parking area.

Cover roofs of structures with shingles, slate, asphalt, aluminum, wood, or related materials;
Spray roofs, sidings, and walls with material to bind, seal, insulate, or soundproof sections of structures;
Inspect problem roofs to determine the best repair procedures;
Install partially overlapping layers of material over roof insulation surfaces, using chalk lines, gauges on shingling hatchets, or lines on shingles;
Attach roofing paper to roofs in overlapping strips to form bases for other materials.
